## Stage Handoff — Plan → Build

Before invoking ship, write a **structured handoff** so the build stage
gets a compact summary instead of re-reading the entire plan.

Write `TASK_DIR/handoff-plan.json` with this structure:
```json
{
  "schema_version": 1,
  "source_phase": "plan",
  "target_phase": "build",
  "task_id": "task-NNN",
  "summary": "<2-4 sentence summary of the plan: what will be built, key approach, constraints>",
  "decisions": [{"what": "...", "why": "...", "classification": "mechanical|taste"}],
  "risks": [{"description": "...", "mitigation": "...", "severity": "low|medium|high"}],
  "open_items": [{"description": "...", "owner": "builder|user", "priority": "high|medium|low"}],
  "artifacts_produced": ["plan.md"],
  "scope_changes": [],
  "created_at": "<ISO 8601 UTC>"
}
```

Then update `workflow-state.json` → `artifacts.handoff` to `"handoff-plan.json"`.

If `workflow-state.json` does not exist, skip the update — handoff is optional.

